We recommend that Management:

1. Instruct the Municipal Engineering Office strictly observe the afore-cited regulation to furnish the Office of the Auditor of certified copies of the suspension orders for its immediate determination if the grounds for suspension is reasonable or not;

2. Direct the Bids and Awards Committee (BAC), through its secretariat, to submit all contracts, together with all the supporting documents forming part thereof, within 5 days from its perfection to the Auditor to enable the latter to conduct auditorial review, before these contracts are forwarded to COA, Regional Office for technical evaluation;

3. Direct Management submit the required supporting documents to effect the necessary evaluation and inspection of the completed infrastructure projects to ascertain the reasonableness of the project costs and regularity of the transactions as required in COA Circular No. 2009-001 dated February 12, 2009; and

4. Instruct the implementing office to fast track the implementation of the projects so that targeted beneficiaries can enjoy the intended benefits may derived therefrom.

